cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI

This paper is about regularization techniques for neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The use of energy minimization and the Thomson problem as inspiration suggests a focus on optimization and mathematical modeling, which are often associated with the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed regularization to several challenging tasks, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
